text.text:
Fort of Akluj
The name Akluj came from Shri Akalai Devi. Solapur to Akluj is approximately 118 km and 169 km from Pune.
This fort is located on the banks of the river Neera.
This fort was restored under the guidance of Babasaheb Purandare. It features army statues on the coast, mural sculptures of Shivaji Maharaj’s life, scenes of his coronation and birth as well as models of important forts. Totally nice project done.

Free ample parking in front of the fort.

text.text: Akalaidevi Temple in Akluj is a serene and spiritually uplifting destination. Nestled amidst lush greenery, this temple exudes tranquility and charm. The intricate architecture and vibrant colors of the temple are a visual delight. It's a place where you can find solace and immerse yourself in the divine aura. Whether you're a devotee or a traveler, Akalaidevi Temple offers a peaceful and enriching experience, making it a must-visit in Akluj. Don't miss the opportunity to explore this cultural gem.

text.text: This is gramdevi of Akluj town. This very old temple at bank of Nira river. Small dam built up on river created good backwater reservoir near temple. Though newly built temple is very nicely done & maintained properly it's not having charm of old heritage & architecture. Temple premises & garden around it is very beautiful. Very nice time to spend some time with family. If you visit here at time of sunset 🌅 it's worth watching. Enjoy visit to this auspicious temple & have completed your wishes.
